cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as keyphrase extraction. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as keyphrase extraction is a sub-task of information retrieval. Additionally, the paper proposes a machine learning framework for feature learning, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of a graph-based representation for the document could also suggest a connection to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
